Cameron Says He Wants People to Feel Better Off, Keep More Money

-- B y   R o b e r t   H u t t o n
-- 
2011-10-04T07:19:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/cameron-says-he-wants-people-to-feel-better-off-keep-more-money.html
U.K. Prime Minister  David Cameron 
said he wanted people to feel better off at the end of his
government’s deficit-reduction program. “I do want people to
feel better off,” Cameron told BBC Radio 4 today from
Manchester, northwest  England , where his  Conservative Party  is
holding its annual conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
